FBIS4-26801 "drchi123_e_94002" FBIS-CHI-94-123 Daily Report 26 Jun 1994 Southeast Asia & Pacific XINHUA Cites Burmese Official on Eliminating Drug Abuse XINHUA Cites Burmese Official on Eliminating Drug Abuse 111 Operations Against Warlord Khun Sa OW2606150094 Beijing XINHUA in English 1436 GMT 26 Jun 94 OW2606150094 Beijing XINHUA English BFN [Text] Yangon [Rangoon], June 26 (XINHUA) -- Myanmar [Burma] Government armed forces conducted 111 operations against drug warlord Khun Sa's armed group in Shan State, eastern Myanmar, from May 11 to June 24, the official radio reported here tonight. During the battles, 196 Myanmar armymen were killed, other 375 were wounded, according to the report. The report also said that the government army found 250 dead bodies of the Khun Sa armed group, and seized a lot of arms and ammunition. Khun Sa is a drug warlord in the notorious golden triangle region which borders Myanmar, Laos and Thailand.
